2. Quantum Threat Analysis

2.1 Quantum Attack Vectors

2.1.1 Cryptographic Attacks

```
Quantum Attack                    Classical Complexity   Quantum Complexity   Break Time (1M Qubits)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RSA-2048 Factoring               O(e^(1.9·ln(N)^(1/3)))  O((log N)^3)        8 hours
Elliptic Curve Discrete Log      O(√p)                   O((log p)^2)        3 hours
Symmetric Key Search (AES-256)  O(2^n)                  O(2^(n/2))          2^128 operations
Hash Function Collision          O(2^(n/2))              O(2^(n/3))          Reduced by 67%
```

2.1.2 AI/ML Vulnerabilities

· Quantum Adversarial Attacks: Quantum-generated adversarial examples
· Model Extraction: Quantum algorithms for faster model theft
· Training Data Inference: Quantum-enhanced membership inference
· Gradient Inversion: Quantum reconstruction of training data

2.1.3 Network Protocol Exploits

· Quantum Man-in-the-Middle: Real-time decryption of TLS sessions
· Session Hijacking: Quantum prediction of session tokens
· Protocol Downgrade: Quantum forcing of weak protocols

2.2 Quantum Attack Surfaces

```
Attack Surface          Classical Threat        Quantum Threat          Mitigation Strategy
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Key Exchange           MITM, Replay           Shor's Algorithm        Lattice-based KEM + QKD
Digital Signatures    Forgery, Tampering     Quantum Forgery         Multi-algorithm signatures
Encryption            Brute-force             Grover's Algorithm      AES-512 + Quantum RNG
Random Generation     Entropy weakness        Quantum predictability  Quantum RNG + Entropy mixing
AI/ML Models          Adversarial attacks     Quantum adversarial     Quantum neural networks
Network Protocols     Protocol flaws          Quantum downgrade       Quantum-resistant protocols
```

