5. Quantum AI for Cybersecurity

5.1 Quantum Neural Network Architecture

5.1.1 QNN Design

```
Layer Type             Qubits      Gates           Purpose
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input Encoding         n          Angle encoding   Classical → Quantum
Variational Circuit    2n         RY, CZ, CRZ      Feature extraction
Entanglement Layer     n(n-1)/2   CNOT, SWAP       Quantum correlation
Measurement            n          Pauli bases      Quantum → Classical
Classical DNN          3n units   ReLU, Softmax    Decision making
```

5.1.2 Training Algorithm

```
Algorithm: Hybrid Quantum-Classical Backpropagation

1. Initialize quantum circuit parameters θ
2. For each batch:
   a. Encode data: |ψ⟩ = U(x)|0⟩^⊗n
   b. Apply variational circuit: |ψ'⟩ = V(θ)|ψ⟩
   c. Measure: ŷ = ⟨ψ'|M|ψ'⟩
   d. Compute loss: L = f(ŷ, y)
   e. Quantum gradient: ∇θL = (⟨ψ'|M|ψ'⟩ - ⟨ψ'|M|ψ'⟩)/2
   f. Update: θ ← θ - η∇θL
3. Repeat until convergence
```

